from PIL import Image
import numpy as np

# Open an image file
image_path = '1280-x-1024-Desktop-Wallpaper.jpg'  # Replace with the actual path of your image
image = Image.open(image_path)
grayscale_image = image.convert('L')

# Convert the image to a NumPy array
image_array = np.array(grayscale_image)

# Flatten the image array into a 1D array
image_1d_array = image_array.flatten()

print("Original image shape:", image_array.shape)
print("Flattened 1D array shape:", image_1d_array.shape)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Open image files
image_path2 = 'output2.jpg'  

image1 = Image.open(image_path)
image2 = Image.open(image_path2)

# Create a figure with two subplots
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(30, 15))  # Increase the figsize for larger images

# Plot the first image on the left subplot
axes[0].imshow(image1)
axes[0].set_title('input image')
axes[0].axis('off')

# Plot the second image on the right subplot
axes[1].imshow(image2, cmap='gray')
axes[1].set_title('output image')
axes[1].axis('off')

# Adjust spacing between subplots
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
